  "narrative": "LBO model for PROJECT-HELIOS with an entry date of 2026-07-15 (USD millions). The sponsor acquires the business at 10.0x LTM EBITDA of 200.0 for a purchase enterprise value of 2,000.0; with 2.0% transaction fees and 2.0% financing fees, total uses are 2,064.0. The capital structure funds 1,200.0 of new debt across a Term Loan B (4.0x) and Senior Notes (2.0x) at 6.0x opening leverage, with the sponsor-equity plug of 864.0 balancing sources to uses. Over a five-year hold the operating forecast grows revenue and EBITDA on explicit driver assumptions, cash interest accrues on beginning debt balances, and free cash flow above the minimum-cash floor sweeps the Term Loan B. In the base case the business exits at 10.0x EBITDA for an enterprise value of 2,676.5, which after 787.4 of net debt leaves 1,889.1 of sponsor exit equity \u2014 about 2.19x MOIC and a 16.9% IRR on a single entry-to-exit cash flow. The upside and downside cases flex growth, margin, and the exit multiple per the documented scenario adjustments and bracket the base case (downside about 1.29x / 5.2%, upside about 3.27x / 26.7%). Every scenario ties out (sources & uses, the debt and cash roll-forwards, the exit walk, and the return math) and returns are monotonic across the three cases. These figures are model outputs conditional on the stated assumptions, each carried in the assumptions register with a provenance tag and citation; a qualified human must review the assumptions and the capital structure before any use. Illustrative leveraged-buyout model for analytical purposes only; not investment advice, not a recommendation to make, hold, or exit any investment, not a guarantee of any return, IRR, or multiple, and not an investment-committee approval. Outputs depend entirely on the stated assumptions, which a qualified human must review."
